# React Conventions

**Single stack (prototype + production):** Vite + React 19 + Capacitor — `src/App.jsx`.

Canonical architecture: `docs/architecture/tech-stack.md`  
Integration patterns: `docs/architecture/best-practices.md`  
UI design system: `docs/design/ui-reference.md` + `.cursor/rules/ui-design-system.mdc`

The UI hardens into production on this stack. There is no migration to Expo, Next.js, or React Native.

## Components

- Functional components with hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`)
- Match existing patterns: inline styles, compact component names, co-located data constants
- Minimize scope — change only what the story requires
- Extract to `src/features/` when a story grows beyond a single screen

## Code quality

- Pass `npm run lint` (ESLint flat config in `eslint.config.js`)
- ES modules (`import`/`export`), no CommonJS in `src/`
- Unused vars error unless prefixed with `_` or uppercase (`varsIgnorePattern: '^[A-Z_]'`)
- Client env vars: `VITE_*` only; never bundle service-role or API secrets

## Capacitor

- Use `@capacitor/core` platform checks when branching native vs web behavior
- Status bar and keyboard plugins are integrated in `App.jsx` — follow existing usage
- Run `npm run build && npx cap sync` before native testing

## Tests

- Name tests traceable to acceptance criteria: `test_STORY_X_Y_AC1_*`
- Colocate under `tests/` or `src/__tests__/`

## Files

- Entry: `src/main.jsx`
- App shell: `src/App.jsx`
- Styles: `src/index.css`, `src/App.css`
